criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Histologically proven gastric or GE junction adenocarcinoma;

          -  Age: 18 to 70;

          -  ECOG 0-2;

          -  Adenocarcinoma of the stomach or GE junction according to staging classification TNM
             Scannographic: T3-4 N0/N + M0 ;

          -  Completion of baseline quality of life questionnaire

          -  Adequate bone marrow functions (ANC ≥ 1,500/ul, blood platelet ≥ 100,000/ul,
             haemoglobin ≥ 10g/dl);

          -  Adequate renal functions(serum creatinine ≤ 1.5mg/dl)

          -  liver functions (serum bilirubin ≤ 1.5UNL, AST/ALT ≤ 3 times(normal value)

          -  Written informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Previous chemotherapy;

          -  Active infection requiring antibiotics

          -  Pregnant, lactating women

          -  Psychiatric illness, epileptic disorders

          -  Concurrent systemic illness not appropriate for chemotherapy

          -  History of other malignancy within 5 years except for non-melanoma skin cancer, cervix
             in situ carcinoma
